{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"HTML guidelines","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/MDN/Guidelines/Code_guidelines/HTML","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n  <ol>\n    <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/About\">About MDN</a></li>\n    <li class=\"toggle\">\n        <details>\n            <summary>Contributing to MDN</summary>\n            <ol>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Contribute/Getting_started\">Get started on MDN</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Contribute\">Contributing to MDN</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Contribute/Howto\">Things you can do</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Contribute/Localize\">Localizing MDN</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Guidelines\">Guidelines</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Structures\">Content structures</a></li>\n             </ol>\n        </details>\n    </li>\n  </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following guidelines cover how to write HTML for MDN code examples.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"in_this_article","title":"In this article","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"#doctype_and_metadata\">Doctype and metadata</a>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"#doctype\">Doctype</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#document_language\">Document language</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#document_characterset\">Document characterset</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#viewport_meta_tag\">Viewport meta tag</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li><a href=\"#general_markup_coding_style\">General markup coding style</a>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"#use_lowercase\">Use lower case</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#trailing_slashes\">Trailing slashes</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#quoting_attributes\">Quoting attributes</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#use_double_quotes\">Use double quotes</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#boolean_attributes\">Boolean attributes</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#class_and_id_names\">Class and ID names</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#entity_references\">Entity references</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"doctype_and_metadata","title":"Doctype and metadata","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> The guidelines in this section apply only when you need to show a complete HTML document. Most of the time you won't need to do this; a snippet is usually enough to demonstrate a feature. When using the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Structures/Code_examples#traditional_live_samples\">EmbedLiveSample macro</a>, just include the HTML snippet; it will automatically be inserted it into a full HTML document when displayed.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"doctype","title":"Doctype","isH3":true,"content":"<p>You should use the HTML5 doctype. It is short, easy to remember, and backwards compatible:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token doctype\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;!</span><span class=\"token doctype-tag\">DOCTYPE</span> <span class=\"token name\">html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"document_language","title":"Document language","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Set the document language using the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes#attr-lang\"><code>lang</code></a> attribute on your <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/html\"><code>&lt;html&gt;</code></a> element:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>en-US<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is good for accessibility and search engines, helps with localizing content, and reminds people to use best practices.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"document_characterset","title":"Document characterset","isH3":true,"content":"<p>You should also define your document's characterset like so:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>meta</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">charset</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>utf-8<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Use UTF-8 unless you have a very good reason not to; it will cover your character needs pretty much regardless of what language you are using in your document. In addition, you should always specify the characterset as early as possible within your HTML's <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/head\"><code>&lt;head&gt;</code></a> block (within the first kilobyte), as it protects against a rather <a href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/kb/928847\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">nasty Internet Explorer security vulnerability</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"viewport_meta_tag","title":"Viewport meta tag","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Finally, you should always add the viewport meta tag into your HTML <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/head\"><code>&lt;head&gt;</code></a>, to give the example a better chance of working on mobile devices. You should include at least the following in your document, which can be modified later on as the need arises:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>meta</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">name</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>viewport<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">content</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>width=device-width<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>See <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Viewport_meta_tag\">Using the viewport meta tag to control layout on mobile browsers</a> for further details.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"general_markup_coding_style","title":"General markup coding style","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"use_lowercase","title":"Use lowercase","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Use lowercase for all element names and attribute names/values, as it looks neater and means you can write markup faster:</p>\n<p>This is good:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>nice<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>This looks nice and neat<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is not so good:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>P</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">CLASS</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>WHOA-THERE<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Why is my markup shouting?<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>P</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"trailing_slashes","title":"Trailing slashes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Don't include XHTML-style trailing slashes for empty elements, as they are unnecessary and slow things down. They can also break old browsers if you are not careful (although from what we can recall, this hasn't been a problem since Netscape 4).</p>\n<p>This is fine:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>input</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">type</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>text<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>hr</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The slashes are not needed:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>input</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">type</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>text<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>hr</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"quoting_attributes","title":"Quoting attributes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>You should put all attribute values in double quotes. It is tempting to omit quotes since HTML5 allows this, but markup is neater and easier to read if you do include them. For example, this is better:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>images/logo.jpg<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">alt</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>A circular globe icon<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>no-border<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>…than this:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span>images/logo.jpg</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">alt</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span>A</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">circular</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">globe</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">icon</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span>no-border</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It can also cause problems — in the above example the <code>alt</code> attribute will be interpreted as multiple attributes, because there are no quotes to specify that \"A circular globe icon\" is a single attribute value.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"use_double_quotes","title":"Use double quotes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Use double quotes for HTML, not single quotes:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>important<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Yes<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>important<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Nope<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"boolean_attributes","title":"Boolean attributes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Don't write out boolean attributes in full; you can just write the attribute name to set it. For example, you can write:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code>required\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is perfectly understandable and works fine; the longer version with the value is supported but not necessary:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code>required=\"required\"\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"class_and_id_names","title":"Class and ID names","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Use semantic class/ID names, and separate multiple words with hyphens. Don't use camelCase.</p>\n<p>Good:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>editorial-summary<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Blah blah blah<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Bad:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>bigRedBox<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Blah blah blah<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"entity_references","title":"Entity references","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Don't use entity references unnecessarily — use the literal character wherever possible (you'll still need to escape characters like angle brackets and quote marks).</p>\n<p>As an example you could just write</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>© 2018 Me<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Instead of</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token entity named-entity\" title=\"©\">&amp;copy;</span> 2018 Me<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is fine as long as you declare a UTF-8 character set.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"good_html_examples_on_mdn","title":"Good HTML examples on MDN","isH3":false,"content":"<p>You can find good, concise, meaningful HTML snippets at the top of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference\">HTML reference pages</a> — our interactive examples are generally written to follow these guidelines, although be aware that they may differ in some places as they were mostly written before the guidelines were newly written.</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"In this article","id":"in_this_article"},{"text":"Doctype and metadata","id":"doctype_and_metadata"},{"text":"General markup coding style","id":"general_markup_coding_style"},{"text":"Good HTML examples on MDN","id":"good_html_examples_on_mdn"}],"summary":"The following guidelines cover how to write HTML for MDN code examples.","popularity":0.0013,"modified":"2022-02-18T09:33:58.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Lignes directrices pour le HTML","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"HTML ガイドライン","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/mdn/guidelines/code_guidelines/html","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/mdn/guidelines/code_guidelines/html/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/0160aac0e623dacdce4019205f32f7b3d3e58019","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/MDN","title":"The MDN project"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/MDN/Guidelines","title":"Guidelines"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/MDN/Guidelines/Code_guidelines","title":"Code example guidelines"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/MDN/Guidelines/Code_guidelines/HTML","title":"HTML guidelines"}],"pageTitle":"HTML guidelines - The MDN project | MDN","noIndexing":false}}